Script,ChoiceOfFinesses
window.currentPBSScenario = 'ChoiceOfFinesses';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Choice_Of_Finesses';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for ChoiceOfFinesses');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'ChoiceOfFinesses',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: 21GF-DEFAULT
convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1N
*/
# ----- Declarer (South) — 1NT opener, 4-3-3-3, specific holdings -----
sSpadeKJ   = hascard(south, KS) and hascard(south, JS) and not hascard(south, AS) and not hascard(south, QS)
sHeartA    = hascard(south, AH) and not hascard(south, KH) and not hascard(south, QH) and not hascard(south, JH)
sDiamondA  = hascard(south, AD) and not hascard(south, KD) and not hascard(south, QD)
sClubA     = hascard(south, AC) and not hascard(south, KC) and not hascard(south, JC) and not hascard(south, QC)
sShape4333 = spades(south) == 4 and hearts(south) == 3 and diamonds(south) == 3 and clubs(south) == 3
sHcp       = hcp(south) > 14 and hcp(south) < 18
southHand = sSpadeKJ and sHeartA and sDiamondA and sClubA and sShape4333 and sHcp

# ----- Dummy (North) — game-going response with KJ of clubs -----
nSpadeA    = hascard(north, AS) and not hascard(north, KS) and not hascard(north, QS) and not hascard(north, JS)
nHeartNo   = not hascard(north, AH) and not hascard(north, KH) and not hascard(north, QH) and not hascard(north, JH)
nDiamondK  = hascard(north, KD) and not hascard(north, AD) and not hascard(north, QD) and not hascard(north, JD)
nClubKJ    = hascard(north, KC) and hascard(north, JC) and not hascard(north, AC) and not hascard(north, QC)
nShape3334 = spades(north) == 3 and hearts(north) == 3 and diamonds(north) == 3 and clubs(north) == 4
nHcp       = hcp(north) > 9 and hcp(north) < 13
northHand = nSpadeA and nHeartNo and nDiamondK and nClubKJ and nShape3334 and nHcp

# ----- East — the DANGER hand with long hearts -----
# 5-card heart suit headed by KQ. Too weak to overcall or open weak 2.
eHearts = hearts(east) == 5 and hascard(east, KH) and hascard(east, QH)
eHcp    = hcp(east) < 10
eastHand = eHearts and eHcp

# ----- West — SAFE hand, short in hearts, no entries -----
wHearts = hearts(west) < 3
wHcp    = hcp(west) < 11
westHand = wHearts and wHcp

# Combine
southHand and northHand and eastHand and westHand

action printoneline,
average "Q spades with East " 100 * hascard(east, QS),
average "Q spades with West " 100 * hascard(west, QS),
average "Q clubs with East  " 100 * hascard(east, QC),
average "Q clubs with West  " 100 * hascard(west, QC),
average "East 5 hearts      " 100 * (hearts(east) == 5),
average "West 0-2 hearts    " 100 * (hearts(west) < 3),
average "South HCP          "       hcp(south),
average "North HCP          "       hcp(north),
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Choice of Finesses,\n\
--- Choice of Finesses (3NT)\n\
South opens 1NT (15-17 balanced)，North raises to 3NT，South declares.\n\
\n\
Teaching feature: declarer has TWO finesse opportunities，in different suits.\n\
ONE loses to West (safe — West has no hearts to lead back). The OTHER loses\n\
to East (fatal — East has a 5-card heart suit headed by KQ and will cash it).\n\
\n\
Holdings:\n\
• Spades — KJxx in South，Axx in North. Lead small from dummy toward\n\
  South's KJ. If the finesse fails，WEST wins. ← SAFE.\n\
• Clubs — Axx in South，KJxx in North. Lead small from South toward\n\
  dummy's KJ. If the finesse fails，EAST wins. ← FATAL.\n\
\n\
The decision:\n\
• Take the spade finesse — it loses safely to West.\n\
• Do NOT take the club finesse — it loses fatally to East.\n\
• If you only need one extra trick，the spade finesse alone is enough.\n\
\n\
Even if the spade finesse loses，West can't hurt you: West has at most two\n\
hearts and no way to put East in.\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/avoidance.php\n\
%ChoiceOfFinesses%
